portant features of contemporary film and media culture today.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aFilm remakesxHistory and criticism. 0aFilm remakes-History and criticism. 0aFilm sequels. 4aFilm, Media & Cultural Studies. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / General.2bisacsh1 aBenson, Nicholas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFleury, James, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aForrest, Jennifer, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGrainge, Paul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGray, Jonathan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHanna, Erin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHerbert, Daniel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHills, Matt, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJohnson, Derek, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLoock, Kathleen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMeehan, Eileen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPerkins, Claire, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aProctor, William, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTryon, Chuck, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVerevis, Constantine, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aVerevis, Constantine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEdinburgh University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311078041340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978147445138340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781474451383423Cover